The paper deals with the problem of finding a minimum-weight subgraph that satisfies connectivity requirements, which is a problem in graph theory and optimization. The use of planar graphs and the properties of triconnected planar graphs suggest that the paper may belong to the categories of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CG (Computational Geometry). The problem of finding a minimum-weight subgraph also involves optimization, which suggests that the paper may belong to the category of cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). The paper may also involve some graph theory and combinatorics, which suggests that it may belong to the categories of cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) and cs.NA (Numerical Analysis).
